Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also uses transfer learning and ensemble models, which are common techniques in machine learning, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) likely sub-categories as well. The paper also involves feature learning and image retrieval, which are related to information retrieval, making cs.IR (Information Retrieval) a possible sub-category. Finally, the paper deals with image processing and analysis, which is a common topic in multimedia research, making cs.MM (Multimedia) a possible sub-category.
